tshistorisch aber längst überholte Edition von Klaus Günther Just aus dem Jahre 1955 hinaus.  aThis double volume contains two tragedies by Lohenstein that are based on two events from the reign of the emperor Nero: his mother's murder and the conspiracy of Piso. Presented here to modern standards of critical scholarship are the texts of the 1665 first editions from Breslau. 'Agrippina' and 'Epicharis' are annotated at length here for the first time. Additionally, bibliographic information and translations of all foreign-language "ations in parallel texts make Lohenstein's extensive scholarly annotations accessible for the first time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aLohenstein, Daniel C. von. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aMundt, Lothar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2008z9783110209457oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311018156240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311019387940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110193879423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110193879/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2008  aZDB-23-DGGb2008  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014